'''2MASS J15031961+2525196''' ('''2MASS 1503+2525''') is a nearby [[brown dwarf]] of [[spectral type]] T5.5,{{r|Burgasser2003}} located in constellation [[Boötes]] at approximately 20.7 [[light-year]]s from [[Earth]].{{r|Dupuy2012}}

==History of observations==

===Discovery===
2MASS 1503+2525 was discovered in 2003 by Adam J. Burgasser ''et al.'' in wide-field search for T dwarfs using the [[Two Micron All Sky Survey|Two Micron All Sky Survey (2MASS)]].

==Distance==
Currently the most precise distance estimate of 2MASS 1503+2525 is a [[trigonometric parallax]], published by Dupuy and Liu in 2012: 157.2 ± 2.2 [[milliarcsecond|mas]], corresponding to a distance 6.36 ± 0.09 [[parsec|pc]], or 20.7 ± 0.3 [[light-year|ly]].{{r|Dupuy2012}}

