'''''Deinococcus indicus''''' is a species of [[arsenic]]-resistant bacterium. It is [[Gram-negative]], rod-shaped, non-[[motile]], non-[[sporulation|sporulating]] and red-pigmented, with type strain Wt/1a<sup>T</sup> (=MTCC 4913<sup>T</sup> =DSM 15307<sup>T</sup>).<ref name="Suresh2004">{{cite journal|last1=Suresh|first1=K.|title=Deinococcus indicus sp. nov., an arsenic-resistant bacterium from an aquifer in West Bengal, India|journal=International Journal of Systematic and Evolutionary Microbiology|volume=54|issue=2|year=2004|pages=457–461|issn=1466-5026|doi=10.1099/ijs.0.02758-0|pmid=15023960}}</ref>

