{{Infobox astronaut | name = Oldřich Pelčák | image = Svět knihy 2011 - Oldřich Pelčák.jpg | caption = Oldřich Pelčák in 2011 | type = | nationality = [[Czech Republic|Czech]] | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1943|11|2}} | birth_place = [[Zlín]], [[Czechoslovakia]] | occupation = | rank = | selection = [[List of astronauts by selection#1976|Air Force Group 6]] | space_time = | missions = [[Soyuz 28]] (backup) }}
'''Oldřich Pelčák''' (born November 2, 1943 in [[Zlín]], [[Czechoslovakia]]) was a [[Czech Republic|Czech]] [[cosmonaut]] and [[engineer]]. He graduated from [[Gagarin Air Force Academy|Gagarin Air Force Military Academy]]. In 1976, Pelčák was selected as backup of [[Vladimír Remek]] for the [[Soyuz 28]] mission.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://aktualne.centrum.cz/domaci/fotogalerie/2008/03/06/exkluzivne-remkuv-let-ocima-jeho-nahradnika-pelcaka/foto/126466/ |title=Exkluzivně: Remkův let očima jeho náhradníka Pelčáka |publisher=Aktualne.cz |language=Czech |accessdate=January 30, 2010}}</ref> They were the first cosmonauts who were neither [[Americans]] nor [[Soviets]].
