{{Notability|date=November 2016}}
'''Simon Ratcliffe''' is a South African [[astronomer]] known for his promotion of the [[Square Kilometre Array]] project. The media have dubbed him the "barefoot astronomer" for his habit of working without shoes.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mg.co.za/article/2013-03-12-ska-scientist-dream-team-works-on-big-data-for-big-telescope |title=SKA: Scientist dream team works on big data for big telescope &#124; Sci-Tech &#124; M&G |publisher=Mg.co.za |date=2013-03-12 |accessdate=2015-09-30}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.skatelescope.org/news/big-bang-meets-big-data/ |title=Big Bang Meets Big Data: South Africa Joins ASTRON and IBM to Build the Foundation for a New Era of Computing |publisher=SKA Telescope |date= |accessdate=2015-09-30}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ska.ac.za/releases/20110218b.php |title=Media release: The Barefoot Astronomer |publisher=Ska.ac.za |date=2011-02-18 |accessdate=2015-09-30}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.brandsouthafrica.com/tvc/profiles/22-simon-ratcliffe.html |title=A project of Brand South Africa - Simon Ratcliffe |publisher=Brandsouthafrica.com |date= |accessdate=2015-09-30}}</ref>

