{{BLP sources|date=March 2010}} {{Infobox astronaut | name =Yuri Georgiyevich Shargin | image =Shargin 02.jpg | type =[[Russian Federal Space Agency|RKA]] Cosmonaut | status =Retired | nationality =Russian | birth_date ={{Birth date and age|1960|3|20}} | birth_place =[[Engels (city)|Engels]], Russia | rank =Lieutenant Colonel, Russian Space Forces | occupation =[[Aeronautics]] | selection =[[List of astronauts by selection#1996|1996 RKA Group]] | time =9d 21h 30m | mission =[[Soyuz TMA-5]], [[Soyuz TMA-4]] | insignia =[[Image:Soyuz TMA-5 Patch.png|30px]] |}} '''Yuri Georgiyevich Shargin''' ({{lang-ru|Юрий Георгиевич Шаргин}}) is a retired cosmonaut of the Russian Space Forces.
He was born March 20, 1960, in [[Engels (city)|Engels]], [[Saratov Oblast]], [[Russian SFSR]]. He is divorced and has two children.
Shargin graduated from the Military Engineering Academy for Aeronautics and Astronautics located in Leningrad. He is a lieutenant colonel in the Russian Space Forces.
He was selected as a cosmonaut on February 9, 1996.
He was selected in 2004, to be the flight engineer on the [[Soyuz TMA-5]] mission to the [[International Space Station]]. Shargin was the first Russian military cosmonaut on board and had a secret mission.{{Citation needed|date=February 2007}}
